Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.25,0:34:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,standard of desktops for many
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.79,0:34:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,years but we're going to raise
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.08,0:34:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the bar once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.82,0:34:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And as always on the iMac, it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.32,0:34:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,starts with the display.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.49,0:34:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the 4K and 5K Retina
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.46,0:34:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,iMac displays with their high
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.84,0:34:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,resolution, excellent brightness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.79,0:34:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and P3 color gamut, are the best
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.80,0:34:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,displays on any desktop.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.29,0:34:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're going to make them
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.71,0:34:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,even better.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.99,0:34:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So these new displays are now
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.78,0:34:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be 500 nits.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.38,0:34:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 43% brighter than the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.28,0:34:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,previous generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.81,0:34:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the first time, we're
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.46,0:34:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,going to support 10-bit
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.55,0:34:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,dithering, which means these
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.86,0:34:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,displays can reproduce up to a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.21,0:35:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,billion colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.59,0:35:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, your content is going to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.78,0:35:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,look more true to life than ever
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.24,0:35:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,before.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.57,0:35:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in addition, we've got some
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.98,0:35:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,great internal updates for these
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.55,0:35:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,iMacs.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.29,0:35:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll start with the CPU
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.50,0:35:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because the whole line is moving
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.83,0:35:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to Intel's 7th-generation Core
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.67,0:35:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Processor, also known as Kaby
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.55,0:35:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.17,0:35:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Kaby Lake gets this better
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.49,0:35:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,base and turbo frequencies for
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.22,0:35:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,more performance as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.86,0:35:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,hardware-based 10-bit HEVC
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.17,0:35:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,decode which is great for
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.59,0:35:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,playing back high quality video.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.02,0:35:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, these iMacs are
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.32,0:35:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,getting a boost when it comes to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.40,0:35:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,memory capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.77,0:35:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the 21.5-inch systems can now
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.00,0:35:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,be configured with up to 32 gigs
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.77,0:35:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.58,0:35:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And the 27-inch can go all the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.18,0:35:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,way up to 64 gigabytes of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.57,0:35:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.22,0:35:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of those are twice what the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.45,0:35:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,previous generation can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.98,0:35:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, fast storage has always
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.52,0:35:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,been a key part of the iMac.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.99,0:35:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, we're going to now make
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.08,0:35:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,our Fusion Drive standard on all
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.17,0:35:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,27-inch configs.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.28,0:35:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's also going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.61,0:35:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,standard on the high-end
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.81,0:35:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,21.5-inch config as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.20,0:35:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, our SSD options are
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.37,0:35:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be up to 50% faster and
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.43,0:36:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,now available up to 2 terabytes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.83,0:36:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And the iMacs are getting an IO
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.43,0:36:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,upgrade as well because we're
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.44,0:36:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,giving them two USB-C connectors
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.75,0:36:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,which support Thunderbolt 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.47,0:36:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And we think our customers
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.64,0:36:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,especially our Pro users are
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.16,0:36:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,really going to love this
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.94,0:36:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can do some cool
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.00,0:36:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,things like hook up a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.25,0:36:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,high-performance RAID array and
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.97,0:36:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,an external 5K display at the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.97,0:36:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.66,0:36:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, let's talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.97,0:36:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,graphics.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.50,0:36:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you heard earlier, we're
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.91,0:36:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,investing heavily in graphic
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.39,0:36:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,software technologies like Metal
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.09,0:36:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,2.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.43,0:36:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we're also investing in
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.21,0:36:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,graphics hardware.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.17,0:36:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And every configuration in this
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.93,0:36:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,new iMac line is going to get a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.24,0:36:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,big bump in its graphics
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.07,0:36:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.35,0:36:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll start with the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.10,0:36:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,entry-level iMac.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.19,0:36:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this system gets a boost in
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.50,0:36:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,its integrated GPU by way of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.39,0:36:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Intel's Iris Plus Graphics which
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.21,0:36:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,now has 64 megabytes of eDRAM.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.64,0:36:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And the performance that we're
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.63,0:36:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,getting out of this is pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.55,0:36:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,amazing because this system is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.10,0:36:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,up to 80% faster in graphics
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.20,0:36:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,than the previous generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.52,0:36:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause and Cheering ]
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.81,0:36:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now next up is the 21.5-inch
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.44,0:37:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,iMac with Retina 4K display.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.30,0:37:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And the big news here is that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.94,0:37:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to be moving to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.06,0:37:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,discrete graphics and making it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.52,0:37:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,standard on all 4K iMacs.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.93,0:37:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's going to come-- There
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.38,0:37:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.58,0:37:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's going to come in this
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.94,0:37:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Radeon Pro series GPUs with up
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.36,0:37:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to 4 gigabytes of VRAM.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.66,0:37:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, this move to discrete
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.11,0:37:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,graphics yield to pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.05,0:37:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,spectacular performance increase
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.97,0:37:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,because this new system is up to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.62,0:37:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,three times faster than the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.26,0:37:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,previous generation for
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.29,0:37:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,graphics.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.52,0:37:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause and Cheering ]
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.23,0:37:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, lastly, we have our 27-inch
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.45,0:37:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,iMAc.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.72,0:37:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is our most popular
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.94,0:37:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,desktop for our Pro customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.93,0:37:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So obviously, it's going to get
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.21,0:37:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a bump in graphics today as
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.35,0:37:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,well.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.04,0:37:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's going to have this
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.00,0:37:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Radeon Pro 500 series GPUs with
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.57,0:37:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,up to 8 gigabytes of VRAM.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.08,0:37:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, we get a great
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.19,0:37:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,performance uplift.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.98,0:37:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, this 27-inch iMac can
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.69,0:37:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,now deliver up to 5.5 teraflops
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.19,0:37:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of graphics to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.11,0:37:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause and Cheering ]
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.21,0:37:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Which makes it a great platform
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.42,0:37:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for VR content creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.42,0:37:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, we've seated some
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.67,0:38:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,developers with this new iMac in
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.48,0:38:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,High Sierra so that we could see
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.38,0:38:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,what they can do with virtual
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.69,0:38:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,reality on the Mac.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.20,0:38:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm really excited that we
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.36,0:38:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,can give you a demo of some of
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.62,0:38:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,this amazing work right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.65,0:38:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'd like to invite up on the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.87,0:38:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,stage, here from Industrial
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.27,0:38:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Light & Magic is academy-award
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.26,0:38:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,winning visual effects artist
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.79,0:38:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and Chief Creative Officer John
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.86,0:38:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Knoll.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.51,0:38:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,John.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.48,0:38:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause and Cheering ]
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.95,0:38:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.52,0:38:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause and Cheering ]
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.20,0:38:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,At Lucasfilm's ILMxLab, story,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.02,0:38:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,concept design and technical
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.28,0:38:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,development are all intertwined.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.27,0:38:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They come together for us to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.26,0:38:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,create immersive experiences for
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.73,0:38:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,people to enjoy at home, in
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.65,0:38:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,cinemas and at theme parks.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.80,0:38:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I've always done my art and
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.52,0:38:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,development on the Mac so I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.79,0:38:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,really excited about these new
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.05,0:38:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,iMacs.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.37,0:38:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I truly love the platform so I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.98,0:38:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,especially excited to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.18,0:38:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,share some of our VR content
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.63,0:38:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,created on these new iMacs and
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.59,0:38:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Epic's Unreal Engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.33,0:38:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm joined by Lauren Ridge, an
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.88,0:38:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Epic programmer who will be at
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.03,0:39:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,backstage driving our demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.54,0:39:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Working together, we can work in
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.19,0:39:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,real-time to create an immersive
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.12,0:39:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,experience as we step inside the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.01,0:39:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"Star Wars" universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.63,0:39:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Lauren's backstage so we
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.97,0:39:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,can show you the environment
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.10,0:39:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.39,0:39:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And now, we're going to show
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.67,0:39:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you from my perspective.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.59,0:39:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, we are in the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.88,0:39:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mustafar.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.72,0:39:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to the native VR support
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.45,0:39:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in macOS High Sierra, I can use
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.72,0:39:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Unreal Engine's editor to create
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.31,0:39:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,content inside the VR
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.28,0:39:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.35,0:39:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the first time, it's all
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.08,0:39:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,powered by my Mac.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.99,0:39:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,On my left motion controller, I
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.47,0:39:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,have my Radial Menu, which
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.79,0:39:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,accesses my artist palette.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.67,0:39:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now on the right, I have the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.96,0:39:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,laser I use to interact with the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.37,0:39:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,world and some fire here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.89,0:39:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's try that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.70,0:39:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.11,0:39:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Very nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.83,0:39:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do some set dressing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.12,0:39:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.75,0:39:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.26,0:39:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me open my content browser.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.78,0:39:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It has all the assets I need to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.56,0:39:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,dress my scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.25,0:39:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I saw that landing spot
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.40,0:39:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for an imperial shuttle over
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.44,0:39:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,here so let's bring one of those
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.71,0:39:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.05,0:40:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We've actually set up the smart
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.17,0:40:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,assets so they know exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.39,0:40:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,where to come in for their
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.14,0:40:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.96,0:40:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Great, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.55,0:40:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we go wide?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.19,0:40:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Sure. I can grab on to them
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.22,0:40:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,with two hands and scale myself
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.77,0:40:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,up.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.97,0:40:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I can also use this to rotate
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.72,0:40:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the world around me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.32,0:40:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Very cool.
