Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.72,1:16:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The team is going to keep
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.50,1:16:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,working hard at that.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.58,1:16:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have a lot more coming
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.46,1:16:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for the remainder of the year.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.98,1:16:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I've highlighted a bunch of
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.11,1:16:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,things here.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.99,1:16:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just point out one of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.67,1:16:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You can read some of your
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.95,1:16:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,favorite things up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.10,1:16:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A big request in developers is
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.32,1:16:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,called phased releases.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.14,1:16:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now when you--
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.63,1:16:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Woo!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.80,1:16:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes, woo for phased releases,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.08,1:16:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.69,1:16:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Phased releases means, when you
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.03,1:16:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,submit an app, you can choose if
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.20,1:16:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you want it to be phased over
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.55,1:16:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,time so it doesn't hit your
